  "text": "Preparation of tissue homogenates. Total tissue homogenates were prepared as described previously [CITATION_1] . Briefly, skeletal muscles (ϳ200-300 mg) were pulverized and homogenized with a Polytron (Brinkmann Instruments, Westbury, NY) at a speed of 6.5 (11.0 full scale) for three 20-s periods at 4°C in a buffer containing 10 mM Tris ⅐ HCl (pH 7.5), 1 mM EDTA, protease inhibitors (500 M phenylmethylsulfonyl fluoride), 1 M leupeptin, 1 M pepstatin, and 10 M E-64. Protein concentrations were determined by a protein assay (Bio-Rad, Melville, NY).",
